
                          AMC-Pico-8 Oscilloscope


The CAEN ELS AMC-Pico-8 Oscilloscope is an application which offers a graphical
environment for easy interfacing with AMC-Pico-8 board. It displays the captured
current signals in time and frequency domain, calculates the signal statistics
(mean value and standard deviation), enables selection of the analog front-end
range and control of acquisition and trigger options.



Installation
=============

The AMC-Pico-8 oscilloscope requires Python3, PyQt5 framework and PyQtGraph
library.

The command to install the required modules on Ubuntu/Debian are the following:

Python
------

    sudo apt-get install python3


PyQt5
-----

    sudo apt-get install python3-pyqt5 python3-pyqt5.qtsvg


PyQtGraph
---------

    git clone -b pyqt5 https://github.com/pyqtgraph/pyqtgraph.git
    cd pyqtgraph
    sudo python3 setup.py install



Usage
=====

Run the oscilloscope.py from terminal.
